<doc id="41158" wikidata="Q5457857" url="?curid=41158" title="Flat weighting">
<text>In a noise-measuring set, flat weighting is a noise weighting based on an amplitude-frequency characteristic that is flat over a frequency range that must be stated. 

==Notes==
* &quot;Note 1:&quot; Flat noise power is expressed in dBrn (f1 − f2) or in dBm (f1 − f2).
* &quot;Note 2: &quot;3 kHz flat weighting&quot;&quot; and &quot;15 kHz flat weighting&quot; are based on amplitude-frequency characteristics that are flat between 30 Hz and the frequency indicated.

==References==
