<doc id="41185" wikidata="Q5502839" url="?curid=41185" title="Frequency-change signaling">
<text>In telecommunications, frequency-change signaling is a telegraph signaling method in which one or more particular frequencies correspond to each desired signaling condition of a telegraph code. The transition from one set of frequencies to the other may be a continuous or a discontinuous change in the frequency or phase.

==See also==
*Frequency-shift keying
*Frequency modulation

