<doc id="41272" wikidata="Q16911402" url="?curid=41272" title="Interchange circuit">
<text>In telecommunications, an interchange circuit is a circuit that facilitates the exchange of data and signaling information between data terminal equipment (DTE) and data circuit-terminating equipment (DCE). 

An interchange circuit can carry many types of signals and provide many types of service features, such as control signals, timing signals, and common return functions.

